---
/**
 * MeetChris — left bio column, center portrait, right second column.
 * Copy: bundle text + brand correction ("Value-First mindset", not "values-first").
 * Bundle's "values-first mindset" was a typo against brand rule "always Value-First, never Values-First."
 */
---

<section class="cc-meet">
  <img class="cc-meet-ring cc-meet-ring-l" src="/assets/ellipse-14.webp" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
  <img class="cc-meet-ring cc-meet-ring-r" src="/assets/ellipse-17.webp" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
  <h2 class="cc-meet-headline">Meet Chris</h2>

  <div class="cc-meet-grid">
    <div class="cc-meet-col cc-meet-col-left">
      <p>
        Hey! I&rsquo;m Chris Carolan, and I help leaders and businesses move from industrial-age operations to AI-empowered organizations. I do this with a Value-First mindset so you can activate your team&rsquo;s capabilities instead of replacing them.
      </p>
      <p>
        What makes my work different isn&rsquo;t just my understanding of HubSpot, AI, or business systems. It&rsquo;s how I think.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="cc-meet-portrait" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="/assets/meet-portrait.webp" alt="" />
    </div>

    <div class="cc-meet-col cc-meet-col-right">
      <p>
        I see patterns across domains that most people miss. I question assumptions others have stopped noticing. And I bring a kind of optimism that makes change feel possible, even when the decision in front of you feels impossible.
      </p>
      <p class="cc-meet-emphasis">Most of all, I care.</p>
      <p>
        About the people inside the system. About helping leaders make better decisions. About building companies that actually work for the humans inside them, not just the spreadsheet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cc-meet {
    position: relative;
    padding: 120px clamp(24px, 20vw, 390px) 60px;
    overflow: hidden;
    /* Section-level cosmic band — Figma places swirl image at y=4187 behind
       MeetChris. Gradient veil fades the texture into navy at top + bottom so
       it reads as a self-contained band, not bleeding into neighbors. */
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, #1C1B2D 0%, rgba(28, 27, 45, 0) 35%, rgba(28, 27, 45, 0) 65%, #1C1B2D 100%),
      url('/assets/bg-cosmic-particles.jpg') center center / cover no-repeat;
  }
  .cc-meet-headline {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    font-family: var(--cc-font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 4.2vw, 64px);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--cc-mirinda);
    margin: 0 0 30px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .cc-meet-grid {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.4fr 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .cc-meet-col {
    font-family: var(--cc-font-body);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--cc-pearl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 18px;
  }
  .cc-meet-col-right {
    padding-top: 80px;
  }
  .cc-meet-col p {
    margin: 0;
  }
  .cc-meet-emphasis {
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  /* Feathered Figma portrait (baked alpha) — no crop, no rounded rect */
  .cc-meet-portrait {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .cc-meet-portrait img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    /* Transparent cutout — blends on the dark section as-is (Figma has no baked
       feather). A whisper of bottom fade hides the photo's hard lower crop. */
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, #000 86%, transparent 100%);
    mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, #000 86%, transparent 100%);
    -webkit-mask-repeat: no-repeat;
    mask-repeat: no-repeat;
    -webkit-mask-size: 100% 100%;
    mask-size: 100% 100%;
  }
  /* Figma ring decorations replacing the old solid discs */
  .cc-meet-ring {
    position: absolute;
    z-index: 0;
    height: auto;
    pointer-events: none;
    user-select: none;
  }
  .cc-meet-ring-l { left: -340px; top: 80px; width: 560px; }
  .cc-meet-ring-r { right: -320px; bottom: 40px; width: 520px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .cc-meet-ring { display: none; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .cc-meet {
      padding: 60px 24px;
    }
    .cc-meet-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 30px;
    }
    .cc-meet-col-right {
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .cc-meet-portrait {
      max-width: 480px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
